    slug: 'recognising-grooming-what-parents-need-to-know',
    title: 'Recognising Grooming: What Every Parent Needs to Know',
    category: 'Child Protection',
    excerpt: 'Grooming is a gradual, deliberate process designed to go unnoticed. Understanding how it works is the most powerful thing parents can do to protect their children.',
    metaDescription: 'Parents\' guide to recognising grooming: how the process works, warning signs in children and adults, online and in-person risks, and what to do.',
